<br>
=====Begin Post========<br>
<br>
While not many people seem to like the Sojourner line, i'm having some fun with it....but there are some setbacks in it that seem needless to me. So, I figured i'd post them here for feedback.<br>
<br>
1) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Unending Breath:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Currently has a 3 second cast time. If a group mate dies and is rezzed they lose the buff...if the Sojourner is combat, they cannot restore water breathing and the group mate must waste a potion. Why not make this an insta? I may be wrong, but there appears to be no balance reason to make it casted. I'd also suggest that it be increased to an hour long just like potions were a couple patches ago.<br>
<br>
2) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Unmake Crystalseed:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This needs to be GTAE just like Reveal Crystalseed. As it stands now, it requires a target. The problem being that traps can be triggered from behind walls and doors and due to Line of Sight being required to target them, there is no way to disable them. Thus making the Crystalseed line worthless.<br>
<br>
3) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Ancient Transmuter:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Please, PLEASE remove the 30 minute recast timer. With all the ML and quest items that we are forced to carry, I barely have any room for loot and my inventory fills up LONG before that 30 minute timer expires. It seems pointless to have a timer considering that what he sells comes stacked and is extremely light weight. I'd wager that he is used more for selling than for buying anyways. There appears to be no balance reason behind the 30 minute timer.<br>
<br>
4) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Gateway:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> By Mythic's own description, the sojourner is supposed to expedite the travel of yourself and realm mates...but in the spell lines, realm mates seem to be forgotten. Please change this to send a confirmation to group mates asking if they wish to be ported as well.<br>
<br>
5) <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Resistance of the Ancients:</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This group resist buff currently has a 1 minute duration which makes this ability all but worthless considering that Essence styles can be spammed repeatedly forever. Essence styles are also area effect while this resist buff is group effect. If this buff is meant to be the counter to essence dmg, its horribly unbalanced. IMO, the resist buff should be changed to work just like existing resist buffs (group effect, 10 minute timer, recast anytime)<br>
<br>
Thoughts?  <p>Sideshow lvl50 ML6 Skald</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etherag>Etherag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/26/04 7:29 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=800.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Suggestions for the Sojourner line...Cross Posted</span><hr size=1> Both I and a guildmate took the Sojourner ML line.  I liked the idea of it being more group benefit oriented than just adding to my battle skills.<br>
<br>
1)        Agree.  It’s hard to get out of combat to try and help someone out with your breath spell.  Also agree it should be a hour just like the potions (no reason to penalize the ML)<br>
2)        I feel that reveal crystalseed and unmake crystalseed should be one ML ability.  It’s unique in that it’s the only ML (or skill in the game) that requires 2 levels to be of use.  One to find them and one to remove them.  It would be like a purge requiring a pre requisite of “locate effect” or some other such nonsense.<br>
3)        Transmuter.  Its great that we have someone to sell to but I think we are missing out on half of what this ability is designed to do.  As a skald I CANT use arrows or poisons so why do I want a merchant that sells them.  More useful would be a potion merchant (Maybe better yet a link to a house merchant as an option.)  Ideally I want to get things useful to me (power potions, heal potions or the ingredients and ability to make them).<br>
4)        Agree.  MLs are reported to help us help out realm mates.  Group port is what is needed.<br>
5)        Again agree.  Needs to be in line with other resists not so “hope I hit it at the right time” spell<br>
<br>
Rosie, procedural question but, who represents the MLs?  Are each class TL also their ML TL or is their a new ML TL?  Thanks <br>
